# StandardRB Automatic Enforcement

## Automated Formatting

When working with Ruby files, StandardRB formatting must be applied automatically:

**Always run before committing:**
```bash
bin/standardrb --fix
```

**Integration with development workflow:**
- Apply StandardRB formatting before any commit containing Ruby files
- Use the project's existing `bin/standardrb` script for consistent formatting
- Ensure all team members follow the same formatting standards

## Scope

This rule applies to:
- All Ruby files (`*.rb`)
- Rake files (`*.rake`)
- Any file containing Ruby code

## Enforcement

The workspace rules already define comprehensive StandardRB guidelines. This Cursor rule ensures automated enforcement of those standards during development.
